== Cheesy Chorizo Crusted Sea Bream with Roasted Potatoes, Asparagus and Aioli ==

Preheat your oven to 200°C. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pop the potatoes onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @olive oil{2%tsp}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Zest and halve the @lemon{½} and roughly chop the @chorizo{60%g} into small pieces. Pop the chorizo, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and @olive oil{1%tbsp} into a #bowl{}. Add the @hard Italian style cheese{25%g}(grated), lemon zest and season with @pepper{}. Mix together.

Put three quarters of the @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} into a bowl and set aside. Lay the @sea bream fillets{2}, skin-side down, onto a baking tray lined with #baking paper{}. Spread the remaining mayo over the flesh of the fish, then spoon over the chorizo crumb. Press it down with a #spoon{}. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until the crumbs are golden and the fish is cooked, ~{10-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw fish. The fish is cooked when opaque all the way through.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1/2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Put the garlic into the bowl with the mayo and squeeze in some lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper. Mix together then set aside.

> TIP: Use less garlic if you don't like raw garlic.

Trim the bottom 2cm from the @asparagus{200%g} and discard. Halve the asparagus widthways. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large #frying pan{} over medium heat. Once hot, add the asparagus and season with salt and pepper. Fry for ~{1%minute}, then add a splash of water and cover the pan with a #lid{} or some #foil{}. Turn the heat to medium and steam until the asparagus is tender, ~{4-6%minutes}, then remove from the heat.

Serve the crusted sea bream on #plates{} with the potatoes, asparagus and a spoonful of aioli alongside. Chop any remaining lemon into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!

== Apple Crumble Dessert ==

If it isn't already, preheat your oven to 200°C. Peel the @apple{4}, then quarter, core and roughly chop them. Pop into a #medium bowl{} along with the @ground cinnamon{½%tsp} and half the @caster sugar{75%g}. Mix well to ensure the apples are evenly coated. Set aside.

Chop the @unsalted butter{60%g} into 1cm pieces. In a #large bowl{}, combine the @plain flour{72%g} and remaining sugar. Add the chopped butter and rub it in with your fingertips until the mixture resembles breadcrumbs. Stir through the @granola{30%g}. Pop the apple filling into an appropriately sized #ovenproof dish{} and cover evenly with the crumble topping.

Pop the crumble on the top shelf of your oven and bake until the top is golden and the apple is bubbling, ~{35-40%minutes}. Allow to cool slightly before serving with a dollop of @creme fraiche{75%g}. Enjoy!